The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 June is 43,701 (5,036.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 June, there were 518 new confirmed cases (59.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 June, there were 291 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 78% (227 extra cases).
